# Files in this list are committed to git but NOT deployed to Vercel,
# so they will not be reachable at https://www.secondrm.com/<path>.
#
# Keep this list aligned with anything that is "internal documentation"
# or "backend config" — i.e. useful in the repo but should not be served
# as a static asset on the public site.

# --- Internal documentation ---
README.md
DESIGN.md
LICENSE
grepp/

# --- Env templates (no secrets, but still internal) ---
.env.example

# --- Firebase backend config (deployed via `firebase deploy`, not Vercel) ---
firebase.json
firestore.rules
functions/

# --- Build / package metadata ---
# NOTE: package.json must remain available to Vercel at build time so it can
# install `firebase-admin` and `node-fetch` for api/form/submit.js. It will be
# served at /package.json by the static handler. That only leaks declared
# dependency versions, which are also visible in the deployed function bundle,
# so we accept that exposure rather than break the build.
# (Intentionally NOT excluded: package.json, package-lock.json)

# --- TLS / signing material ---
# Belt-and-braces: also blocked by .gitignore from being added in future,
# but if any *.pfx / *.pem / *.key is currently tracked it must not ship.
*.pfx
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.crt
serviceAccount*.json
firebase-adminsdk*.json

# --- Editor / agent scratch ---
.claude/
.cursor/
